The paper deals with approximation algorithms for TSP and its variants, which are classic topics in theoretical computer science. The use of dynamic programming and graph theory techniques suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The study of approximability and complexity of optimization problems is also relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper involves graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which are topics covered in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
